{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-programs-js","path":"/programs/program-metrics.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Program metrics show how healthy a program is. They enable hackers to see various statistics regarding:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Program information</li>\n<li><a href=\"#response-efficiency-metrics\">Response efficiency</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#program-statistics\">Program statistics</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The metrics are displayed on the right side of the program's security page.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Program metrics\"\n        title=\"Program metrics\"\n        src=\"/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/0b533/program-metrics-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/fac75/program-metrics-1.png 125w,\n/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/63868/program-metrics-1.png 250w,\n/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/0b533/program-metrics-1.png 500w,\n/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/1d69c/program-metrics-1.png 750w,\n/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/00d43/program-metrics-1.png 1000w,\n/static/aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a/6c68b/program-metrics-1.png 1888w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"displaying-program-metrics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#displaying-program-metrics\" aria-label=\"displaying program metrics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Displaying Program Metrics</h3>\n<p>To display program metrics on your security page:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <strong>Program Settings > Program > Customization > Metrics Display</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select the statistics you want to display on your security page.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Update</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 81.6%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Program metrics-2\"\n        title=\"Program metrics-2\"\n        src=\"/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/0b533/program-metrics-2a.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/fac75/program-metrics-2a.png 125w,\n/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/63868/program-metrics-2a.png 250w,\n/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/0b533/program-metrics-2a.png 500w,\n/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/1d69c/program-metrics-2a.png 750w,\n/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/00d43/program-metrics-2a.png 1000w,\n/static/074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3/d7ceb/program-metrics-2a.png 1446w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"response-efficiency-metrics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#response-efficiency-metrics\" aria-label=\"response efficiency metrics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Response Efficiency Metrics</h3>\n<p>Response efficiency metrics include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Average time to first response</li>\n<li>Average time to triage</li>\n<li>Average time to resolution</li>\n<li>Average time to bounty</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The averages are calculated by the last 90 days. These metrics give hackers a better idea of how responsive a program is. Learn more about <a href=\"response-target-metrics.html\">response efficiency metrics</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"program-statistics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#program-statistics\" aria-label=\"program statistics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Program Statistics</h3>\n<p>Program statistics are calculated over a programâ€™s lifetime. They set realistic expectations with hackers and security teams for how active your program is. Within the program statistics section of your security page, hackers can view:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Item</th>\n<th>Details</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Total bounties paid</td>\n<td>Total bounties paid can be a strong indicator that a bounty program is active and healthy.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Average bounty</td>\n<td>The average bounty serves as rough guidance for how much a hacker can expect in return for a valid report. It's displayed as a range from the 45th to 55th percentile.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Top bounty range</td>\n<td>Displayed as a range from the 90th to 100th percentile.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reports resolved</td>\n<td>The total number of valid reports that have been resolved.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hackers thanked</td>\n<td>The total number of hackers that have submitted valid reports.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<blockquote>\n<p><i>Note: Any reports filed by a security team's members will not be reflected in the metrics.</i></p>\n</blockquote>","frontmatter":{"path":"/programs/program-metrics.html","id":"programs/program-metrics","title":"Program Metrics","description":null},"headings":[{"value":"Displaying Program Metrics"},{"value":"Response Efficiency Metrics"},{"value":"Program Statistics"}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}